The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Timeout

 A one-of-its-kind event to appear on the city?s social calendar, The Racehorse Show promises to generate brilliant synergy by complimenting the royal passion of racehorses with the shine and sparkle of precious gems and jewellery. At the show, The Royal Calcutta Turf Club (RCTC) will auction two-year old horses that have been sourced from various leading stud farms across the country. Untrained babies, they will be trained to become fine young steeds and shall subsequently participate in races towards the end of the year. Internationally-acclaimed racing commentator Cyrus J. Madan will conduct the auction. Interspersed with the auction sales is an Images India presentation of precious jewellery in diamonds, emeralds and rubies by Vasundhara ? the Jewellery Boutique. Hosted by RCTC and Vasundhara, in association with Glen Drummond and Accord Advertising.

 Event: Racehorse and jewellery show 

When: Today at 8 pm 

Where: Royal Calcutta Turf Club, Calcutta Racecourse (Members stands) 

